The paper analyzes the security of the Stellar consensus protocol, which is a blockchain protocol. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the structure of quorum slices and the influence of nodes, which are related to distributed computing and network protocols, suggesting cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as likely categories. The paper also uses metrics to measure the influence of nodes, which is related to data analysis and machine learning, suggesting cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of deleting nodes on the system, which is related to graph theory and algorithms, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible category.
